reviewText: I ordered the glutes and cardio DVD. I got the DVD and it had the right label but it was the legs and abs workout. I contacted them and I was not a satisfied customer!  Will never buy from them again!

I love doing Zumba. I have purchased 2 of the Target Zone DVDs so far. I will purchase be buying more. I just wish they would produce more tapes. I will keep buying them as long as they keep making them.
It's is okay. I am happy with it. And on top of everything it was cheap. It is what I wanted.
The Samsung adaptive cell phone charger is awesome.  I am very impressed with how fast it charges my cell phone.  On a scale from 1 to 10, I would give it a 10.
It's Cheaper to buy it as a set ... I got ripped off ... Paid 3x's as much!
Way too difficult to follow as a beginner not familiar with zumba.  Don't buy unless you are proficient in the basics and are looking for a way to do zumba in the comfort of your own home...
A nice disc, but not for beginners.
wow!  i wanted a work out for home.  man this dvd really keeps you moving.  gets me motivated for the day.
Like the video. Really dislike the fact that it is all salsa music. I don't mind it but would of been nice to know I probly would of ordered something different if I would have known

I am very unhappy with this purchase. I was under the impression that it was a 3 DVD collection. Thats what it said when I ordered it. I opened up my package to find the DVD in a cracked cheap clear DVD case.  I would never of paid almost $25 for one DVD when amazon has plenty of others for a lot cheaper. There's no contact number for this company. Everything is through email. I sent them an email and they responded back to me with a short rude email. I am very upset and will NEVER buy from Twisterfitness again!
I ordered this DVD thinking it was a new one but it is the same as the Target Zones Abs & Legs that I already own.  Love it BUT it is no different.
I like upbeat Zumba classes and was hoping to get that same experience at home. This Zumba video is pretty slow motion and not the workout that I was looking for.
